{"id": "duc04-testb-32:27#82", "contents": "The Justice Department will counter that antitrust law is intended to protect consumers, and therefore, practices that provide short-term benefits but ultimately drive up prices should not be allowed. The department will argue that monopolists should use the least exclusionary means possible to achieve their goals. Experts agree that the courts will subject Microsoft's restrictive contracts with Internet companies to a balancing test, but the outcome is uncertain. A balancing test would weigh the benefits of one-click access to Internet sites and bundled features against the harm of diminished competition in the markets for browsers and operating systems."}
